'''Albert Léon Guérard''' (1880–1959) was a prominent scholar of Comparative Literature. Guérard taught at [[Stanford University]] for many years.<ref name="Stanford Historical Society - Memorial Resolution - Albert Leon Guérard">{{cite web|url=https://purl.stanford.edu/vk330bk2164 |title=Stanford University Faculty Senate - Memorial Resolution - Albert Leon Guérard |publisher=[[Stanford University]] |accessdate=April 29, 2018 }}</ref> A prolific author, he published works on French and European civilization and [[world literature]].<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.vqronline.org/essay/albert-l%C3%A9on-gu%C3%A9rard-1880-1959-styles-humanist |title=Albert Léon Guérard (1880-1959): the Styles of A Humanist |author=Sholom J. Kahn |year=1989 |journal=The Virginia Quarterly Review}}</ref>
