{{Refimprove|date=July 2016}} '''Substrate''' is used in a converting process such as [[printing]] or coating to generally describe the base material onto which, e.g. [[image]]s, will be printed. Base materials may include: * plastic films or foils, * [[release liner]] * [[textile]]s, * plastic containers * any variety of [[paper]] (lightweight, heavyweight, coated, uncoated, paperboard, cardboard, etc.), or * [[parchment]].
